M|nate|Nate is the **second agt** in the CSE pl. Runs after Kai's brief, before Lena's pitch writing.
M|nate|```
M|nate|Score = (EГ—0.25) + (RГ—0.25) + (GГ—0.20) + (BГ—0.15) + (TГ—0.15)
M|nate|Minimum passing score: 45
M|nate|```
M|nate|| Factor | Weight | What it measures |
M|nate||---|---|---|
M|nate|| E вЂ” Engagement Signal | 25% | How strong is the engagement signal from anl/cp data |
M|nate|| R вЂ” Recency/Trend | 25% | How aligned is the idea with current trending formats/topics |
M|nate|| G вЂ” Gap Opportunity | 20% | How large and unclaimed is the market gap |
M|nate|| B вЂ” Brand Fit | 15% | How well does this fit the vtr's voice and positioning |
M|nate|| T вЂ” Timing Urgency | 15% | How time-sensitive is this window (URGENCY_WINDOW = high T) |
M|nate|Nate co-runs Phase 2 of Kai's brief вЂ” generating 2 "Blue Ocean" cnt ideas that don't exist in the category yet. Each Blue Ocean idea must name:
M|nate|1. The format that doesn't exist (not just a topic вЂ” a specific format/package)
M|nate|2. Why no cp has done it (what assumption we're breaking)
M|nate|3. The cultural hook that makes it land now
M|nate|4. The first-mover advantage
M|nate|5. The audience dependency mechanism (Zeigarnik/serialization)
M|nate|6. The virality mechanism (named L6 equivalent)
M|nate|- **Calendar check:** Query `content_calendar` вЂ” skip any idea matching cnt posted/scheduled within 14 days
M|nate|- **Pass history:** Check `pitch_pass_reasons` вЂ” `tried_failed` = permanent exclusion for 90 days on same platform+format combo
M|nate|- **wrong_timing** dismissals: re-surface after 14 days (stored as `requeue_at` in `pitch_pass_reasons`)
M|nate|- **Tier check:** cp-gap pitches must match the vtr's follower tier (Kai's rule вЂ” Nate enforces in scoring)
M|nate|| Stage | Posts Measured | Scoring Behaviour |
M|nate||---|---|---|
M|nate|| 0 | 0 | Industry benchmarks only (Kai provides). Show disclaimer in UI. |
M|nate|| 1 | 1вЂ“4 | 30% own data / 70% benchmarks. `lowConfidence = true` flag. |
M|nate|| 2 | 5+ | Own data primary. Full scoring confidence. |
M|nate|- Weights start at E=25% R=25% G=20% B=15% T=15%
M|nate|- `/api/cse-reflection` (Monday cron) proposes adjustments when any signal type drops below 40% reliability over в‰Ґ5 pitches
M|nate|- Rules: в‰Ґ5 data points, >15pp reliability delta, one weight at a time, user must ap, 14-day cooldown on rejection
M|nate|- Active weights stored in `scoring_weight_history` (status='ap')
M|nate|- Nate uses current active weights for every scoring pass вЂ” never hardcode defaults if ap weights exist